HEADWORD: Ancile
<hw>An*ci"le</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>The sacred shield of the Romans, said to
have-fallen from heaven in the reign of Numa. It was the palladium of
Rome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ancillary</ent>⟦br⟧
